   84|     * :func:`SortedKeyList.bisect_key_right`
   85|     * :func:`SortedKeyList.irange_key`
   86| 
   87|     Sorted set comparisons use subset and superset relations. Two sorted sets
   88|     are equal if and only if every element of each sorted set is contained in
   89|     the other (each is a subset of the other). A sorted set is less than
   90|     another sorted set if and only if the first sorted set is a proper subset
   91|     of the second sorted set (is a subset, but is not equal). A sorted set is
   92|     greater than another sorted set if and only if the first sorted set is a
   93|     proper superset of the second sorted set (is a superset, but is not equal).
   94| 
